# Project Rules System

This file serves as an index and documentation for the modular rules system. It should NOT be set to `alwaysApply: true`.

## Active Modules

The following modules are available in the `rules/` directory. Copy the ones relevant to your project into your project's `.cursor/rules/` directory.

- `000-core.mdc` - Minimal universal principles (always-apply)
- `900-context.mdc` - AI memory and context management (always-apply)

### Optional Modules (`rules/modules/`)
- `frontend-react.mdc` - React/Next.js frontend patterns
- `backend-node.mdc` - Node.js/Express/Fastify API rules
- `python.mdc` - Python-specific rules (e.g., FastAPI/Flask)
- `testing.mdc` - Test requirements and best practices
- `docs.mdc` - Documentation standards

Reference `CURSOR-RULES-SETUP-GUIDE-2025.md` for detailed setup and best practices.